From: Shlomi Marco <s.marco@rubycomm.com>
Date: Sun, 02 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: arm64: dts: rockchip: nanopi-zero2: Enable USB

Enable USB2 PHY, EHCI, OHCI and DWC3 (xHCI) controllers on the
FriendlyElec NanoPi Zero2.

The board has one USB-A host port (via EHCI/OHCI + u2phy_host) and
one USB OTG port (via DWC3 + u2phy_otg). The DWC3 is configured in
OTG mode limited to high-speed since the combo PHY is used for PCIe
(M.2 WiFi slot), leaving no USB3 SuperSpeed lane available. The extcon
binding to u2phy enables coordinated role switching between the DWC3
and USB2 PHY OTG state machines.

The usb2_host_5v regulator and usb20_host1_pwren pinctrl are already
defined in the board DTS but were previously unused.

Signed-off-by: Shlomi Marco <s.marco@rubycomm.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3528-nanopi-zero2.dts | 28 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 28 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3528-nanopi-zero2.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3528-nanopi-zero2.dts
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3528-nanopi-zero2.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3528-nanopi-zero2.dts
@@ -349,3 +349,31 @@
 	pinctrl-0 = <&uart0m0_xfer>;
 	status = "okay";
 };
+
+&u2phy {
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
+&u2phy_host {
+	phy-supply = <&usb2_host_5v>;
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
+&u2phy_otg {
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
+&usb_host0_ehci {
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
+&usb_host0_ohci {
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
+&usb_host0_xhci {
+	extcon = <&u2phy>;
+	maximum-speed = "high-speed";
+	snps,dis_u2_susphy_quirk;
+	status = "okay";
+};
-- 
Armbian

